f=Executive Office/vista/marketplace/north-star-metric/references/nsm-framework-guide.md · h1:NSM Framework Guide=reference three overlapping NSM frameworks (Sean Ellis NSM, Amplitude NSM, Lean Analytics OMTM), math input metrics, role anti-metrics counter-metrics, worked examples five business archetypes. · pt:2: The five tests=defensible NSM pass five: · h3:Test 1: Customer value=NSM goes up, customer get value? company get activity? · h3:Test 1: Customer value=\| NSM \| Passes? \| Why \| · h3:Test 1: Customer value=\|-----\|---------\|-----\| · h3:Test 1: Customer value=\| "Pages viewed per session" \| Mixed \| Could mean useful exploration OR confused navigation \| · h3:Test 1: Customer value=\| "Tasks completed per WAU" \| Yes \| Tasks completed is the value the product delivers \| · h3:Test 1: Customer value=\| "Time on site" \| Mixed \| Engagement OR difficulty completing a task \| · h3:Test 1: Customer value=\| "Revenue" \| No \| Customer value is upstream of revenue \| · h3:Test 2: Strategic alignment=match company makes money? attention NSM transactional business misalignment. · h3:Test Leading, lagging=NSM predict future success? Revenue lagging metric time moves, value-delivery question settled. retention-style engagement-style metric leads. · h3:Test 4: Single number=single number dashboard? "DAU/MAU ratio" one number. "DAU MAU separately" two which fine inputs NSM. · h3:Test 5: Movable=team affect within quarter? team's daily work cannot move metric days, NSM lagging. · pt:Leading indicators depth=leading indicator moves **before** input metric. lag what makes valuable gives team early warning input about move (up down). · h3:Lag thresholds=**Same-day leaders** (sessions, button clicks): move within minutes team's actions. Useful A/B tests incident detection., **Daily leaders** (day-1 retention, first-task completion): move within day. Useful daily standups., **Weekly leaders** (week-1 cohort retention, feature adoption depth): move within week. Useful sprint reviews. · h3:Selecting leading indicators=input, ask: What action user take predicts they affect input? What metric counts action? fast metric move relative input? leading indicator moves after input does, leading co-lagging proxy. · h3:Worked example=**Input:** Week-4 retention (lagging) Possible leading indicators: · h3:Worked example=**Day-1 retention** known tomorrow, **First-session feature adoption count** known within hour, **Time first value** known within minutes, **Signup-flow completion rate** known within minutes · h3:Worked example=four move within hours; week-4 retention takes month. leaders tell you what week-4 look like, weeks before arrives. · h3:Attention archetype: media streaming app=**NSM**: Time spent watching content >=50% completion, **Formula**: NSM WAU (Sessions WAU) (Minutes session) (Completion rate), **Inputs**: WAU, sessions WAU, minutes session, completion rate, **Leading indicators**: Day-1 returning users, autoplay opt-out rate, first-session completion rate, **Anti-metrics**: Time-to-skip seconds median, churn within days first watch, **Counter-metric**: Subscription churn rate 4%/mo · h3:Transaction archetype: marketplace=**NSM**: Weekly gross merchandise value (GMV), **Formula**: NSM Active buyers (Orders buyer) (Average order value), **Inputs**: Active buyers, orders buyer, average order value, **Leading indicators**: Cart-create rate, listing-page conversion rate, repeat-buyer rate days, **Anti-metrics**: Cancellation rate 5%, refund rate 2%, fraud-flagged orders 0.5%, **Counter-metric**: Take rate stable 12% · h3:Productivity archetype: SaaS task management=**NSM**: Weekly active accounts publishing >=1 deliverable, **Formula**: NSM WAA Publisher rate, **Inputs**: WAA, publisher rate, **Leading indicators**: First-deliverable session templates opened week invite-a-teammate rate, **Anti-metrics**: Weekly churn 4%, time-to-publish median min, **Counter-metric**: Server cost published deliverable $0.08 · h3:Communication archetype: messaging app=**NSM**: Weekly active accounts sending >=2000 messages (Slack-style), **Formula**: NSM WAA P(>=2000 msgs week), **Inputs**: WAA, message-volume-per-account distribution, **Leading indicators**: Day-1 messages sent, channels created, integrations added, **Anti-metrics**: Spam-flagged messages 0.1%, abuse-report rate stable, **Counter-metric**: Paid seat conversion 18% · h3:Subscriber archetype: SaaS subscription=**NSM**: Paid weekly active subscribers, **Formula**: NSM Paid subs Weekly active rate, **Inputs**: Paid subs, weekly active rate, **Leading indicators**: Trial-to-paid conversion rate, day-1 paid activation rate, NPS day, **Anti-metrics**: 60-day refund rate 3%, NPS detractor share 25%, **Counter-metric**: Gross margin stable 78% · h2:Further reading=Sean Ellis, "Hacking Growth" (Crown Business, 2017), John Cutler's writing NSMs (Amplitude blog), Alistair Croll Benjamin Yoskovitz, "Lean Analytics" (O'Reilly, 2013), Amplitude's "North Star Playbook" (free download), "The Hard Thing About Hard Things" Ben Horowitz perils mismeasuring product